ate.set(2)\\\",\\n            \\\"[2] state.CAS(2, 3)\\\",\\n            \\\"[3] state.getAndSet(4):3\\\",\\n            \\\"[4] state.lazySet(5)\\\",\\n            \\\"[5] finish\\\",\\n            \\\"[6] 5\\\"\\n        )\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    fun traceActsAsRingBufferAndValidatesCapacity() {\\n        assertThrows(IllegalArgumentException::class.java) {\\n            Trace(0)\\n        }\\n\\n        val trace = Trace(4, TraceFormat { index, event -> \\\"$index=$event\\\" })\\n        trace.append(\\\"a\\\", \\\"b\\\")\\n        trace.append(\\\"c\\\", \\\"d\\\", \\\"e\\\")\\n\\n        assertThat(trace.toString().lines()).containsExactly(\\n            \\\"1=b\\\",\\n            \\\"2=c\\\",\\n            \\\"3=d\\\",\\n            \\\"4=e\\\"\\n        )\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    fun atomicOperationsRemainCorrectUnderContention() {\\n        val counter = atomic(0)\\n        val toggles = atomic(0L)\\n        val owner = atomic<String?>(null)\\n\\n        runConcurrently(workerCount = 6) { workerIndex ->\\n            repeat(1_000) { iteration ->\\n                counter.getAndIncrement()\\n                toggles.update { it xor 1L }\\n                if (iteration == workerIndex) {\\n                    owner.compareAndSet(null, \\\"worker-$workerIndex\\\")\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        assertThat(counter.value).isEqualTo(6_000)\\n        assertThat(toggles.value).isEqualTo(0L)\\n        assertThat(owner.value).startsWith(\\\"worker-\\\")\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    fun locksSerializeCompoundActionsAndSupportReentrancy() {\\n        val lock = reentrantLock()\\n        val guarded = atomic(0)\\n        val monitor = Any()\\n        val log = Collections.synchronizedList(mutableListOf<Int>())\\n\\n        lock.withLock {\\n            lock.withLock {\\n                guarded.value = 1\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        runConcurrently(workerCount = 5) { workerIndex ->\\n            repeat(300) {\\n                lock.withLock {\\n                    val current = guarded.value\\n                    Thread.yield()\\n                    guarded.value = current + 1\\n                }\\n            }\\n            atomicSynchronized(monitor) {\\n                log.add(workerIndex)\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        assertThat(guarded.value).isEqualTo(1 + 5 * 300)\\n        assertThat(log).containsExactlyInAnyOrder(0, 1, 2, 3, 4)\\n    }\\n\\n    private fun runConcurrently(workerCount: Int, action: (Int) -> Unit) {\\n        val start = CountDownLatch(1)\\n        val done = CountDownLatch(workerCount)\\n        val failure = JdkAtomicReference<Throwable?>()\\n\\n        repeat(workerCount) { workerIndex ->\\n            Thread {\\n                try {\\n                    start.await()\\n                    action(workerIndex)\\n                } catch (throwable: Throwable) {\\n                    failure.compareAndSet(null, throwable)\\n                } finally {\\n                    done.countDown()\\n                }\\n            }.apply {\\n                name = \\\"atomicfu-test-worker-$workerIndex\\\"\\n                start()\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        start.countDown()\\n        assertThat(done.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue()\\n        failure.get()?.let { throw it }\\n    }\\n\\n    private data class Box(val name: String, val count: Int)\\n\\n    private class DelegatedState {\\n        private val atomicNumber = atomic(1)\\n        private val atomicEnabled = atomic(false)\\n        private val atomicLabel = atomic(\\\"cold\\\")\\n\\n        var number by atomicNumber\\n        var enabled by atomicEnabled\\n        var label by atomicLabel\\n\\n        fun bumpNumber(): Int = atomicNumber.incrementAndGet()\\n\\n        fun flipEnabled(): Boolean = atomicEnabled.updateAndGet { !it }\\n\\n        fun replaceLabel(newLabel: String): String = atomicLabel.getAndSet(newLabel)\\n\\n        fun snapshot(): String = \\\"$number:$enabled:$label\\\"\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/metadata-forge/logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T01-56-55-311489Z.log:8418:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_04f486376335a4bb0169f16519eca88197a377c104172c4443\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp8WUvkd4CDHq31ywiFZai0-psMsTQJblG9AD23L2hzGxOqJFzx6uhNl31fYn8F4A7JeUp5JbRVpRxLAqXpnvOjwSpWQjoJPFZO2LpxrUvCgiKn6qHuzC46i5kNzb169SawL4cVBepRCWkGXUd_NlEwxRMmoCONK3LE5sb1G5iymJifVsbsew4iUgtG7uXMifiAXwaHsVJ886lAb1c3ZT_vWLSfVjUpPIJ7lbyTGXus94daj7B41qytoD9agkq2Q1WcZF2IL8zODBn2yibEgcW8wohxiC5_W0oQbM4L4feNd0B6uMlnwOzNhGy9GXeoWOwN3dhmwjpZKj1JvksDjOsuJXWaQ2kVlW0R2R27BCB8O5tS-H_U5OtrdRfSq34StZSPSsGUA4X_tS--6BsXHRED3WmWcd5T8ulVsIGXG6fvUvTbrtvSSI0wr-us-kzOOne3iGk8jM-pzpsAgU7z7-w1uZfpFyQmdWzt8625-zB7b_LYFtFHYF-JchfUVaaclN3ye5pxMMJLVkHeDFeb7fJwQVdoDHR0cIQaIqbW9HvfrH_MbrL9tSk8zTBhPK_KQdv5u0zrTZRKkZPwvs9f5e839hVWphRahClV-Zy2kfs6LjYgzujqIT-TTTYHwfoX0Z2_g485sNLNxjzRJj5wlGXd8_jWQlPlm8fR-II-92HOURPiWuvQaW6p27XY3-9qXDZGPNi8dq0d7SMM2dmqBqoVKyCu6QDbhk8HQcfX0ozZgiu9cn6zHb-m4HkJI9kJ9V5PRpMvtRG25KOgAFC09SD5HeqTxGqA9RxZAlJ6jCTTpJXYGwx3MXSWZD6C0DzZjKVohhA8xSWVYxueSWuK6GATUYgvZYrINcv7_viL8SpImD1nVDIBMvi-HUbblm8z653dz3rupoQ4dEMsBAGydw2-qDWaIoheQQQDlPu7wT7CknDRRsPWfCazPPl2mufuZywu6yWwZJPOdJ1ZHlb8pekZrFAGwHL8cbPN7Iy7ZNFvu9zgOSZlfrzAhX5H_fpRtTpuKm0kU8IE0fUxfkIBmvqzp_1O3LvIZgWGNU5jRE8Lgi5U5KOBZQz9QXwAzeYGYWpNgDq6BbBvvq9P4i32fwa_QQZ5oYuBCyWUaprhrP__jxitekRsZ0Ig9K_dnM5nIF4r4c-qsyT8_5hvq5jHTST0AZL7FLjK6B3F3BXx-ygMJGQfQgoXiBOpuHpMQ8Rs-H2EJkJWQJ3GF5jVsEwrZyUJc6Qh_8tK3qnhG3uMGrztSAtdKao4D34Hy0WcbpcHAo_6IRUX4lI6d66H_B4LOx0YLSyo9AnJ9NZSLC7vlZjXybYWlwvJ6E8hkEVgyewwgSgO_vDYoXVHK_ljCHCprLjuEvqeiIqZftfvavE0YLPqYIJpUbfzu-mwhW6usY-17W39ZMoeUQLlgK3kGHeBHbf80ve8nRQPdonwrBXOn5ib9yvTWuswGkGWYtJxk7Lo2mHDNF69ifC8P4zOtPgWjOUXA1iBV0s_CU1Ci